Add a public function called FetchUrl to Effects.calr that simulates a network request. It takes str parameter url and returns str. The function must declare the network read effect.

Use this exact Calor network effect syntax:
§F{f001:FetchUrl:pub}
  §I{str:url}
  §O{str}
  §E{net:r}
  §B{result} "Response from: "
  §R (+ result url)
§/F{f001}

The §E{net:r} declares the network read effect:
- net:r = network read access (GET requests)
- net:w = network write access (POST/PUT requests)
- net:rw = network read/write access

Note: This is a stub implementation. In real code, you would use HttpClient, but the important part is correctly declaring the effect.
